subject: Populate BMC state based on state manager D-bus property
commitMessage:
Populate BMC state based on state manager D-bus property

Currently BMC state hard coded to "On" irrespective of
BMC state.
It's possible that bmc state can struck at NotReady state
and there are other possible BMC states as per state manager

This commit represents all other possible states by reading
state manager CurrentBMCState property.
https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/State/BMC.interface.yaml#L46

Tested by:
GET /redfish/v1/Managers/bmc for different BMC states

Tested by setting CurrentBMCState property to all possible values.

Redfish Validator passed

Signed-off-by: Ravi Teja <raviteja28031990@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I8ceafb7036f41678516ebda3dce5200221bba947

Sorry, should have been clear in that last comment. I think this should be "On" as well. The "State" will indicate the BMC is still "Starting".
